                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d563">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">882.01 Foreign Control/381: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_VSRG1" type="from"
                            >Gilbert</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-09-29T17:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 29, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 29—12:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>274. From <persName corresp="#p_RSJ1">Reber</persName>. My 271, September 28,
                        noon.<note n="73" xml:id="d563fn73">Not printed.</note> I have been asked to
                    inform the chairman how soon the <persName corresp="#p_FHSS1"
                        >Firestone</persName> interests are prepared to negotiate the financial
                    clauses of the plan of assistance, the administrative sections having been
                    accepted by the Liberian representatives. <persName corresp="#p_FHSJ1">Harvey
                        Firestone, Jr.</persName> is in Paris without word from Akron regarding
                    decision there. Please instruct. [<persName corresp="#p_RSJ1"
                    >Reber</persName>.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_VSRG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
